  <section>
    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <FaqAccordion>
      <FaqItem question="What is the easiest pour-over coffee maker for beginners?">
        <p>A simple cone brewer with easy-to-find filters is usually the easiest entry point. If you want fast setup and predictable cleanup, a starter dripper like the V60 01 or a Melitta brewer is generally beginner-friendly.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="Does Chemex make better coffee than V60?">
        <p>It depends on what you like. Chemex often leans cleaner and lighter. V60 can produce a wider flavor range and more control if your grinder and pouring technique are solid.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="Can one grinder work for all pour-over brewers?">
        <p>Yes. A capable burr grinder can cover V60, Chemex, Melitta, and similar brewers. You'll typically grind coarser for slower drawdown systems and finer for faster-draining cones.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="How often should I replace paper filters?">
        <p>Paper filters are single-use. Use a fresh one each brew, rinse before brewing, and keep unopened packs dry to avoid storage odor affecting taste.</p>
      </FaqItem>
    </FaqAccordion>
